# Phase 1b/1c — Homepage redesign (router + directory + multi-league hub)

Branch: claude/musing-aryabhata-c235e5 (worktree). Briefing: handover-homepage-ux.md (audit-only on the parallel worktree). Phase 1a (v1.84.0) shipped the schema foundations (`LeagueVisibility` enum, `User.defaultLeagueId` FK); this phase wires the persona-aware apex on top of those columns, mounted at `/test` for preview before promotion to `/`.

## M1 — HomepageRouter scaffolded at /test

**File structure (all under `src/components/homepage/`):**

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `HomepageRouter.tsx` | Server component. Reads session, calls `resolveHomepagePersona`, branches: `single` → `redirect('/id/<slug>')`, `multi` → `<MultiLeagueHub>`, `directory` → `<LeagueDirectory>`. |
| `LeagueDirectory.tsx` | Server component. Mobile-first card list; "League Directory" literal heading; status pill differentiates Recruiting / Closed. |
| `MultiLeagueHub.tsx` | Server component. Wraps `<Dashboard>` for the active league + injects switcher + handoff via the new `topSlot` prop. |
| `LeagueSwitcherTabs.tsx` | Client component. Pill-strip tab UI (Option A); calls `setUserDefaultLeague` server action + `router.refresh()`. |
| `RecruitingHandoff.tsx` | Server component. Capped (≤2) cards for PUBLIC_OPEN leagues the viewer is NOT in. |
| `actions.ts` | `'use server'` — `setUserDefaultLeague(leagueId)` server action with auth + membership gates. |

**Persona detection (server-side):**

`src/lib/homepageRouting.ts` exposes three functions:

- `getApprovedMembershipsAndDefault({ userId, lineId })` — async DB read. Resolves the canonical User row (accepts either identifier per the v1.80.10 admin-orthogonal-UX shape), reads `defaultLeagueId` + the linked Player's APPROVED current PLMs in a single chain, dedupes by leagueId, sorts alphabetically.
- `classifyPersona({ memberships, defaultLeagueId })` — pure decision function. `0 → directory`, `1 → single`, `≥2 → multi`. The multi branch honours `defaultLeagueId` ONLY when it points at a league the user is still APPROVED in (stale-default fallback to `memberships[0]`).
- `resolveHomepagePersona({ userId, lineId })` — convenience composer; production calls this from `<HomepageRouter>`. Tests typically use the two helpers separately for hermetic decision-rule pinning.

**Mount points:**

- `src/app/test/page.tsx` — minimal mount: `<HomepageRouter />`.
- `src/app/test/directory/page.tsx` — mounts `<LeagueDirectory>` directly with `getDirectoryLeagues()`. Same surface; shareable URL.

`src/app/page.tsx` (apex `/`) is **untouched** — the legacy default-league Dashboard continues to render there. Promotion is a one-line PR (see M5).

## M2 — Directory page + last-selected tracking wired

**Directory data + styling:**

- `src/lib/leagueDirectoryData.ts` reads every `League.visibility !== 'PRIVATE'` row, cached 60s under the `'leagues'` tag (admin `setLeagueVisibility` busts via `revalidate({ domain: 'public' })` → instant directory propagation). Exposes `deriveSeasonLabel(startDate)` purely so unit tests can pin the JST → "'YY 春/秋" derivation without DB.
- Card layout: 14×14 colored-block "thumbnail" using the league abbreviation (no `League.thumbnail` column exists yet — surfacing what we have honestly), name + ball-type + location + season label, status pill. PUBLIC_OPEN → "Recruiting" (primary fill), PUBLIC_CLOSED → "Closed" (surface fill). Mobile-first single column inside the existing `max-w-lg` brand container.

**Last-selected tracking — cheap-write mechanism:**

- `src/lib/userDefaultLeague.ts#touchUserDefaultLeague({ userId, lineId, leagueId })` is fire-and-forget via `waitUntil` from `@vercel/functions` (the same shape `applyToLeague` uses for the v1.79.0 application-received email). Wired into `src/app/id/[slug]/page.tsx` and `src/app/id/[slug]/md/[id]/page.tsx`.
- Three short-circuits keep the cost zero on the hot path: (1) no userId AND no lineId → return immediately, (2) `User.defaultLeagueId === leagueId` → no-op fast path, (3) viewer has no APPROVED + current PLM in the league they're visiting → no write (a logged-in user can't bookmark a league they're not in by visiting it).
- Apex `/page.tsx` does not call this helper — the apex doesn't have per-league context AND remains the legacy untouched default-league surface during the preview window.

**Test pin update:** `tests/unit/v1755_league_details_full_consolidation.test.ts` previously asserted that `getServerSession(authOptions)` was absent from all three page sources. The pin is now scoped to `apex /page.tsx` only; the `/id/[slug]/*` pages legitimately re-introduce the session call to drive `touchUserDefaultLeague`. Documented inline.

## M3 — Multi-league switcher built

**Chose Option A (pill-strip tab UI) over Option B (banner + dropdown).**

Rationale: a 2–4-league user benefits from at-a-glance visibility — every league is one tap away with no extra interaction. A dropdown adds a tap and hides the membership count behind a chevron. On overflow (5+ leagues, currently zero in production) the strip horizontally scrolls via `overflow-x-auto` rather than wrapping, keeping the typography intact.

**Mobile layout:**

- `h-9` pills with `gap-2`, `flex-shrink-0`. Active pill: `bg-primary text-primary-foreground`. Inactive: `bg-surface text-fg-mid hover:bg-surface-md`. `aria-pressed` + `data-active="true"` for testid + a11y.
- Sits inside Dashboard's `topSlot` (new prop on Dashboard, optional + nullable so existing call sites compile unchanged) — that puts it inside the same `max-w-lg` column as everything else, BELOW the fixed Header. Rendering it OUTSIDE Dashboard would push it under the fixed Header (would have been a regression target).
- `useTransition` wraps the switch action so the strip stays interactive while the refresh is in flight; the active pill shows a subtle `animate-pulse` rather than freezing the whole UI.

**Click behaviour:**

1. Optimistic visual swap of the active pill.
2. `setUserDefaultLeague(leagueId)` server action — auth + APPROVED-PLM gate.
3. On `{ ok: true }` → `router.refresh()` re-renders the server component with the new active league.

**Capped recruiting cards (`<RecruitingHandoff>`):**

- Reads `League.visibility = 'PUBLIC_OPEN'` AND `id NOT IN (excludeIds = user's memberships)`.
- Sorted by `updatedAt DESC, id ASC` as the recency proxy. We don't track `recruiting`-toggle history; `updatedAt` is the pragmatic available signal. Documented in the file head.
- `take: 2` — capped per the brief.
- Returns `null` (no surface, no chrome) when zero candidates remain — the hub stays clean for users in every PUBLIC_OPEN league.
- Card visual mirrors the directory's smaller variant: 10×10 abbreviation block + name + location + "Recruiting" pill.

