## M5 — PR pushed + swap-instructions documented

**Exact swap step (a separate one-line follow-up PR after the user reviews the preview at `/test`):**

```diff
--- a/src/app/page.tsx
+++ b/src/app/page.tsx
- import type { Metadata } from "next";
- import { findNextMatchday } from "@/lib/stats";
- import Dashboard from "@/components/Dashboard";
- ...
- export default async function Home() {
-   const leagueId = await getDefaultLeagueId();
-   if (leagueId === null) { ... }
-   ...
-   return ( <Dashboard ... /> );
- }
+ import HomepageRouter from "@/components/homepage/HomepageRouter";
+
+ export default function Home() {
+   return <HomepageRouter />;
+ }
```

The `<HomepageRouter>` already handles the catastrophic-config branch (no leagues → directory shows the empty state) and the persona dispatch. After the swap, `src/app/test/page.tsx` can stay as a permanent test hook OR be removed in the same PR — operator preference.

**Files unchanged by the swap:** `src/app/id/[slug]/page.tsx`, `src/app/id/[slug]/md/[id]/page.tsx` already call `touchUserDefaultLeague` so the swap is purely an apex change.

**CLAUDE.md ledger:** Updated with the v1.85.0 entry summarising the surface, persona shape, and swap-step pointer.
